oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SAND TRANSPORT RATE UNDER WAVE-CURRENT ACTION
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Watanabe, Akira
Isobe, Masahiko
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: transport rate
sediment transport
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Laboratory experiments were conducted to obtain data on sand transport processes and transport rates under combined action of waves and currents using an oscillatory-steady flow tank. The sand transport processes were classified into seven types. Four kinds of non-dimensional flow power parameters were defined, and their linear relations with the non-dimensional net transport rates were found for all the transport types.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 22 (1990): Proceedings of 22nd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Delft, The Netherlands, 1990.
